content:
# optimised for fast refresh of spatial overlays using gpkg
# Base version as of 12 February 2025
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(leaflet.extras)
library(leaflet.extras2)
#library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(shinyjs)
library(munsell)
library(jsonlite)
options(timeout = 60)  # Set global timeout for all requests


# Workaround for Chromium Issue 468227
downloadButton <- function(...) {
  tag <- shiny::downloadButton(...)
  tag$attribs$download <- NULL
  tag
}
# Define UI for application
ui <- navbarPage("Species Explorer", id = "navbar",
                 tabPanel("Map",
                          useShinyjs(),
                          sidebarLayout(
                            sidebarPanel(width = 3,
                                         selectInput("basemap", "Select Basemap:",
                                                     choices = c("OpenTopoMap" = "OpenTopoMap",
                                                                 "OpenStreetMap" = "OpenStreetMap",
                                                                 "ESRI Satellite" = "Esri.WorldImagery",
                                                                 "Esri.WorldShadedRelief" = "Esri.WorldShadedRelief",
                                                                 "CartoDB Positron" = "CartoDB.Positron"),
                                                     selected = "OpenTopoMap"),
                                         selectInput("overlay_map", "Select Overlay:",
                                                     choices = c("None" = "None",
                                                                 "IBRA" = "IBRA",
                                                                 "IBRA_subregion" = "IBRA_sub",
                                                                 #"Ecoregions (WWF)"="Ecoregions (WWF)",
                                                                 "IPA" = "IPA",
                                                                 "250k_MS" = "250k_MS",
                                                                 "100k_MS" = "100k_MS"),
                                                     selected = "None"),
                                         checkboxGroupInput("taxa_selection", "Select Taxonomic Groups:",
                                                            choices = c("Mammal" = "Mammalia",
                                                                        "Bird" = "Aves",
                                                                        "Reptile" = "Reptilia",
                                                                        "Frog" = "Amphibia",
                                                                        "Fish" = "Actinopterygii",
                                                                        "Spiders and Scorpions" = "Arachnida",
                                                                        "Insects" = "Insecta"),
                                                            selected = "Mammalia"),
                                         #Text input for user to enter a year, default is 2000
                                         numericInput("min_year", "Select Minimum Year:",
                                                      value = 2000, min = 1800, max = as.integer(format(Sys.Date(), "%Y")), step = 1),
                                         
                                         hidden(
                                           div(id = "downloaddiv",
                                               actionButton("generateSpecies", "Search Area", width = '100%'),
                                               br(),
                                               downloadButton("downloadData", "Save Shape File", width = '100%'),
                                               br(),
                                               downloadButton("downloadSpeciesCSV", "Save Species List", width = '100%')
                                           )
                                         )
                            ),
                            mainPanel(width = 9,
                                      tags$style(type = "text/css", "#map {height: calc(100vh - 100px) !important; width: 100% !important; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;}
                                      .shiny-download-link, .shiny-action-button { width: 100% !important; }"),
                                      leafletOutput("map")
                            )
                          )
                 ),
                 tabPanel("Species List",
                          tags$p("⚠️Use caution when interpreting these records. Errors in geographic location or species identification may be present,
                                 and a very low number of records for a species in the search area could indicate potential issues. 
                                 Conservation status is based on external data sources, and subspecies may not always match correctly. 
                                 Always review records carefully before relying on them.",
                                 style = "color: blue; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px;"),
                          tableOutput("speciesTable")
                 )
                 
                 
)

# Define server logic
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  # Store selected overlay map to ensure it's redrawn when basemap changes
  selected_overlay <- reactiveVal(NULL)
  
  output$map <- renderLeaflet({
    leaflet() %>%
      leaflet::addProviderTiles(providers[["OpenTopoMap"]]) %>%
      setView(lng = 133.5, lat = -28, zoom = 4) %>%
      addMiniMap(width = 150, height = 150) %>%
      addDrawToolbar(rectangleOptions = TRUE,
                     editOptions = editToolbarOptions(edit = FALSE, remove = TRUE),
                     polylineOptions = FALSE,
                     circleOptions = FALSE,
                     circleMarkerOptions = FALSE,
                     markerOptions = FALSE,
                     singleFeature = TRUE) %>%
      addWMS( #hack to force addWMS to be bound to leaflet in shinylive for use later on. Add empty wms - bug in shinylive?
        baseUrl = "",
        layers = "IBRA7_regions22849",  # specify the layer id(s)
        checkempty = TRUE,
        options = WMSTileOptions(
          format = "image/png", 
          transparent = TRUE
        ),
        group = "overlay"
      )  %>% 
      clearGroup("overlay")  # Clear previous overlay
  
  })
  
   
  # Maintain zoom level when switching basemaps and force overlay redraw
  observeEvent(input$basemap, {
    req(input$map_zoom, input$map_center)  # Ensure zoom and center exist
    
    leafletProxy("map") %>%
      clearTiles() %>%
      addProviderTiles(providers[[input$basemap]]) %>%
      setView(lng = input$map_center$lng, lat = input$map_center$lat, zoom = input$map_zoom)
    
    # Trigger overlay redraw
    if (!is.null(selected_overlay())) {
      redrawOverlay(selected_overlay())
    }
  })
  
  # Function to load and add overlay
  redrawOverlay <- function(overlay_name) {
    leafletProxy("map") %>% clearGroup("overlay")  # Clear previous overlay
    
    if (overlay_name != "None") {
      
      
      overlay <- switch(overlay_name,
                        "IBRA" = "wms|https://gis.environment.gov.au/gispubmap/services/ogc_services/IBRA7_Regions/MapServer/WMSServer|IBRA7_regions22849",
                        "IBRA_sub" = "wms|https://gis.environment.gov.au/gispubmap/services/ogc_services/IBRA7_Subregions/MapServer/WMSServer|IBRA7_subregions12045",
                        #"Ecoregions (WWF)" = "Ecoregions (WWF)_optimized.gpkg",
                        "IPA" = "wms|https://gis.environment.gov.au/gispubmap/services/ogc_services/Indigenous_Protected_Areas/MapServer/WMSServer|Indigenous_Protected_Areas57724",
                        "250k_MS" = "file|Mapsheets_250k.geojson",
                        "100k_MS" = "file|Mapsheets_100k.geojson")
      
      vals <- strsplit(overlay, "\\|")[[1]]
      type <- vals[1]
      location <- vals[2]
      layer <- vals[3]
      
      if (type == "file"){
        overlay_file <- file.path("shapefiles",location )
        if (file.exists(overlay_file)) {
          overlay <- st_read(overlay_file, quiet = TRUE)
          
          leafletProxy("map") %>%
            addPolygons(data = overlay, 
                        group = "overlay", 
                        fillOpacity = 0, 
                        color = "blue", 
                        weight = 1, 
                        label = ~as.character(NAME))
        } else {
          showNotification("Overlay file not found!", type = "error")
        }
      }
      else if (type == "wms"){
        leafletProxy("map") %>%
          addWMS(
            baseUrl = location,
            layers = layer,  # specify the layer id(s)
            checkempty = TRUE,
            options = WMSTileOptions(
              format = "image/png", 
              transparent = TRUE
              ),
            group = "overlay"
          )
      }
    }
  }
  
  # Observe overlay selection and store it in reactiveVal()
  observeEvent(input$overlay_map, {
    selected_overlay(input$overlay_map)  # Store current selection
    redrawOverlay(input$overlay_map)     # Draw overlay immediately
  })
  
  observeEvent(input$map_draw_new_feature, {
    show("downloaddiv")
  })
  
  observeEvent(input$generateSpecies, {
    if (is.null(input$taxa_selection) || length(input$taxa_selection) == 0) {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "No taxa selected!",
        "Please select at least one.",
        easyClose = TRUE,
        footer = NULL
      ))
      return()
    }
    req(input$map_draw_new_feature)
    req(input$taxa_selection)
    
    
    # geo <- input$map_draw_new_feature$geometry$coordinates[[1]]
    # lng <- map_dbl(geo, `[[`, 1)
    # lat <- map_dbl(geo, `[[`, 2)
    geo <- input$map_draw_new_feature$geometry$coordinates[[1]]
    lng <- sapply(geo, function(pt) pt[[1]])
    lat <- sapply(geo, function(pt) pt[[2]])
    

    # Build WKT polygon string
    coords_str <- paste(paste(lng, lat, sep=" "), collapse=",")
    #wkt <- "POLYGON ((123.648833 -26.667096,123.648833 -23.160563,127.870876 -23.160563,127.870876 -26.667096,123.648833 -26.667096))" 
    wkt <- sprintf("POLYGON((%s))", coords_str)
    
    # Build ALA API URL
   
    base_url <- "https://api.ala.org.au/occurrences/occurrences/facets/download?"
   
    
    taxa <- paste0('(class:"', input$taxa_selection, '")', collapse = " OR ") 
    taxa <- paste0("&fq=",taxa)
    year <- input$min_year
    
    # ALA API uses fq for filters, e.g. fq=taxon_name:...&fq=year:[2000 TO *]
    # For demonstration, filter by class and year
    #POLYGON((123.648833 -26.667096,123.648833 -23.160563,127.870876 -23.160563,127.870876 -26.667096,123.648833 -26.667096))
    year <- paste0("[", year, " TO *]")
    url <- paste0(base_url,'fq=','year:',year,taxa,'&wkt=', wkt, '&qualityProfile=ALA&emailNotify=false&sourceTypeId=2004&reasonTypeId=10&email=mark.cowan@curtin.edu.au&facets=speciesID&lookup=true&count=false&synonym=false&lists=false') 
    #derivied from atlas_spcecies(). Returns a csv
    #url <- "https://api.ala.org.au/occurrences/occurrences/facets/download?fq=(year:[2000 TO *] AND -(year:\"2000\"))AND(lsid:\"https://biodiversity.org.au/afd/taxa/e9e7db31-04df-41fb-bd8d-e0b0f3c332d6\")&wkt=MULTIPOLYGON (((123.6488 -26.6671, 123.6488 -23.16056, 127.8709 -23.16056, 127.8709 -26.6671, 123.6488 -26.6671)))&qualityProfile=ALA&emailNotify=false&sourceTypeId=2004&reasonTypeId=10&email=mark.cowan@curtin.edu.au&facets=speciesID&lookup=true&count=false&synonym=false&lists=false"
    
  
    tmpfile <- tempfile(fileext = ".csv")
    download.file(URLencode(url), tmpfile)#will not be here long as temp file
    # Read CSV (may need to wait for ALA to process large queries)
    species <- read.csv(tmpfile, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)# |> as_tibble()# |> print()

    
    if (nrow(species) == 0) {
      showModal(modalDialog(
        title = "No Records Found",
        "No species records found in the selected area.",
        easyClose = TRUE,
        footer = NULL
      ))
      return()
    }
    base_url2 <- "https://api.ala.org.au/occurrences/occurrences/facets?"
    url2 <- paste0(base_url2,'fq=','year:',year,taxa,'&wkt=', wkt, '&qualityProfile=ALA&facets=species&fsort=count&flimit=10000')
    #url2 <- "https://api.ala.org.au/occurrences/occurrences/facets?fq=(year:[2000 TO *] AND -(year:\"2000\"))AND(lsid:\"https://biodiversity.org.au/afd/taxa/e9e7db31-04df-41fb-bd8d-e0b0f3c332d6\")&wkt=MULTIPOLYGON (((123.6488 -26.6671, 123.6488 -23.16056, 127.8709 -23.16056, 127.8709 -26.6671, 123.6488 -26.6671)))&qualityProfile=ALA&facets=species&fsort=count&flimit=10000"
                 
     # Download CSV (to temp file)
    tmpfile2 <- tempfile(fileext = ".json")
    download.file(URLencode(url2), tmpfile2)
    
    # Read json
    species_counts <- fromJSON(tmpfile2)
    species_counts <- species_counts$fieldResult[[1]]
    
    #join the data
     #species_counts <- species_counts |> rename(scientificName = label)
    names(species_counts)[names(species_counts) == "label"] <- "scientificName"
    
     #species <- species |> rename(scientificName = Species.Name)
    names(species)[names(species) == "Species.Name"] <- "scientificName"
    
     #species <- left_join(species, species_counts, by = "scientificName")
     species <- merge(species, species_counts, by.x = "scientificName", by.y = "scientificName", all.x = TRUE)
    
     #species <- species |> select(Vernacular.Name, scientificName, count, Kingdom, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, everything(), -Taxon.Rank, -Genus)
     # Columns to place first
     first_cols <- c("Vernacular.Name", "scientificName", "count", "Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", "Order", "Family")
     
     # Columns to remove
     exclude_cols <- c("Taxon.Rank", "Genus")
     
     # All remaining columns after excluding first and unwanted
     remaining_cols <- setdiff(names(species), c(first_cols, exclude_cols))
     
     # Final order
     final_cols <- c(first_cols, remaining_cols)
     
     # Subset
     species <- species[final_cols]
     
     #species <- species |> arrange(Kingdom, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, scientificName)
     species <- species[order(species$Kingdom,
                              species$Phylum,
                              species$Class,
                              species$Order,
                              species$Family,
                              species$scientificName), ]
     

    # Load EPBC CSV and keep only required columns
    epbc_data <- read.csv("EPBC.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    colnames(epbc_data) <- trimws(colnames(epbc_data))  # Trim spaces

    # Select only required fields
    #epbc_data <- epbc_data |>
    #  select(`Scientific.Name`, `Threatened.status`, ACT, NSW, NT, QLD, SA, TAS, VIC, WA) |>
    #  rename(scientific_name = `Scientific.Name`, status = `Threatened.status`)
    # Select only required columns
    epbc_data <- epbc_data[c("Scientific.Name", "Threatened.status", "ACT", "NSW", "NT", "QLD", "SA", "TAS", "VIC", "WA")]
    
    # Rename columns
    names(epbc_data)[names(epbc_data) == "Scientific.Name"] <- "scientific_name"
    names(epbc_data)[names(epbc_data) == "Threatened.status"] <- "status"
    

    # Join only selected columns
    #species <- left_join(species, epbc_data, by = c("scientificName" = "scientific_name"))
    species <- merge(species, epbc_data, by.x = "scientificName", by.y = "scientific_name", all.x = TRUE)
    

    # Ensure "status" field exists (NA -> "Not listed")
    species$status[is.na(species$status)] <- "-"

    # Replace NA only for character columns
    char_cols <- sapply(species, is.character)
    species[char_cols] <- lapply(species[char_cols], function(x) replace(x, is.na(x), "-"))

    # Reorder columns to place status after species_name
    #species <- species |> select(Common.name, species_name, status, everything())

    updateNavbarPage(session, "navbar", selected = "Species List")

    output$downloadSpeciesCSV <- downloadHandler(
      filename = function() {
        paste("species_list", "csv", sep=".")
      },
      content = function(file) {
        write.csv(species, file, row.names = FALSE)
      }
    )

     output$speciesTable <- renderTable({ species })
  })
  
  
}


# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
